Sentencas: The synthesis, conductivity properties, area specific resistance (ASR) and thermal expansion behaviour of the layered perovskite SmBaCo2O5+d (SBCO) are investigated for use as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Structural, thermal and electrochemical properties of layered perovskite SmBaCo2O5+d, a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SBCO is prepared and shows the expected orthorhombic pattern.
Titulo: Structural, thermal and electrochemical properties of layered perovskite SmBaCo2O5+d, a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of SBCO exhibits a metal-insulator transition at about 200 degrees C.
Titulo: Structural, thermal and electrochemical properties of layered perovskite SmBaCo2O5+d, a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum conductivity is 570 S cm(-1) at 200 degrees C and its value is higher than 170 S cm(-1) over the whole temperature range investigated.
Titulo: Structural, thermal and electrochemical properties of layered perovskite SmBaCo2O5+d, a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Under variable oxygen partial pressure SBCO is found to be a p-type conductor.
Titulo: Structural, thermal and electrochemical properties of layered perovskite SmBaCo2O5+d, a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The ASR of a composite cathode (50 wt% SBCO and 50 wt% Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-d. SBCO:50) on a Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-d (CGO91) electrolyte is 0.05 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C. An abrupt increase in thermal expansion is observed in the vicinity of 320 degrees C and is ascribed to the generation of oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Structural, thermal and electrochemical properties of layered perovskite SmBaCo2O5+d, a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The coefficients of thermal expansion (CTE) of SBCO is 19.7 and 20.0 x 10(-6) K-1 at 600 and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Structural, thermal and electrochemical properties of layered perovskite SmBaCo2O5+d, a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: By contrast, CTE values for SBCO:50 are 12.3, 12.5 and 12.7 x 10(-6) K-1 at 500, 600 and 700 degrees C, that is, very similar to the value of the CGO91 electrolyte.
Titulo: Structural, thermal and electrochemical properties of layered perovskite SmBaCo2O5+d, a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
